name: CredData
description: CredData is a set of files including credentials in open source projects. vulnerability_report_private_justificati: README at https://git.sr.ht/~seirdy/moac/tree/master/item/README.md includes direct contact info to reach the maintainer, and notes that the maintainer accepts PGP-encrypted emails.
build_justification: Uses a Makefile and the Go toolchain.
test_justification: Uses the Go stdlib's testing tools and runs them in CI.
test_invocation_justification: The Makefile contains test jobs that wrap "go test": https://git.sr.ht/~seirdy/moac/tree/master/item/Makefile
test_most_justification: Test covers just about every line that isn't a panic statement meant to be unreachable.
tests_are_added_justification: OpenBSD builds in CI include a report on test coverage.
tests_documented_added_justification: README encourages contributors to include tests, but notes that if tests aren't included the maintainer will write tests himself.
warnings_justification: Uses golangci-lint and gokart for comprehensive static analysis.
warnings_fixed_justification:
Static analysis tools are run in CI and will trigger a fail if any errors are found. The master branch generally must pass this.

The Makefile also includes a "pre-commit" job that runs linters as well as unit-tests.
warnings_strict_justification: Every golangci-lint check possible is enabled.
know_secure_design_justification: Developer is a bit of a newbie but is familiar with the listed concepts.
know_common_errors_justification: Developer is a bit of a newbie but is familiar with the listed concepts relevant to the project.
crypto_keylength_justification: Default entropy required is 256 bits to match the standard key-length of AES-256, since it expects other software using it to follow these guidelines as well.
crypto_pfs_justification: PFS is unrelated to this software.
crypto_password_storage_justification: Although MOAC deals with passwords, it does *not* deal with password storage. It only  deals with password analysis and generation, delegating storage to other software.
crypto_random_justification: Uses the recommended CSPRNG for Go, crypto/rand.
static_analysis_justification: golangci-lint, gokart, go-consistent, checkmake, shfmt's static analyzer
static_analysis_common_vulnerabilities_j: golangci-lint uses multiple sec-related linters, such as gosec. Gokart is another security-related static analysis tool used by the project.
static_analysis_fixed_justification: All lint jobs must pass for each commit or patch.
static_analysis_often_justification: All lint jobs must pass before a commit and each push triggers a build job.
dynamic_analysis_justification: Tests run with memory/address sanitizers on every commit in CI and as a pre-push hook. Tests without those sanitizers are a pre-commit hook.
dynamic_analysis_unsafe_justification:
This software uses a memory-safe language, Go. Although race conditions happen in Go, this project should be single-threaded and also supports testing with a race detector (leveraging TSan).

If built with CGo, it also supports Clang's memory sanitizer and CFI sanitizer.
dynamic_analysis_enable_assertions_justi: Can build with sanitizers and delegates assertions to unit tests.
dynamic_analysis_fixed_justification: Tests must pass before commits/pushes and in CI after pushing.
general_comments: Project's canonical location is Sourcehut (sr.ht), but it is mirrored across GitHub, GitLab, and Codeberg and accepts contributions through those platforms too. This form doesn't support Sourcehut version-control URLs because they have tildes ("~") so I put a Codeberg URL instead.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: CI build manifests that run on every commit are included in https://git.sr.ht/~seirdy/moac/tree/master/item/.builds
discussion_justification:
- Mailing list: https://lists.sr.ht/~seirdy/moac
- Ticket tracker: https://todo.sr.ht/~seirdy/MOAC

Neither requires running any proprietary software, even in the browser.

MOAC also has GitHub, GitLab, and Codeberg issues/PRs.
no_leaked_credentials_justification: The program "gitleaks" is a pre-commit hook on all of the maintainer's repositories on his workstation.
hardening_justification:
- Project is written in a memory-safe language (Go)
- Project uses memory and race sanitizers in tests
- When linking against C libraries (using CGO), project uses strongly hardened CFLAGS by default.

These mechanisms are found in the Makefile: https://git.sr.ht/~seirdy/moac/tree/master/item/Makefile

sites_password_security_justification: Project does not do any password storage.
vulnerability_report_credit_justificatio: No vulns in the last 12 months
vulnerability_response_process_justifica: README instructs users to report vulns to maintainer by email: https://git.sr.ht/~seirdy/moac/tree/master/item/README.md
coding_standards_enforced_justification: Project enforces strict formatting and compliance with good idioms using golangci-lint, configured for aggressive checks.
build_standard_variables_justification: Makefile extends compiler flags passed to it: https://git.sr.ht/~seirdy/moac/tree/master/Makefile
build_preserve_debug_justification: Debugging information is only stripped when running "make install-bin-strip" or "make install-strip": https://git.sr.ht/~seirdy/moac/tree/master/Makefile
build_non_recursive_justification: The go build system does not perform this behavior by default. The Makefile explicitly lists out the paths to build when building binaries.
build_repeatable_justification:
Since this project doesn't use CGO and pre-sets all flags (including -trimpath), builds are easily reproducible.

Go makes such builds easily reproducible by default: https://blog.filippo.io/reproducing-go-binaries-byte-by-byte/
See https://git.sr.ht/~seirdy/moac/tree/master/Makefile for the build flags.

CI jobs produce binaries that can be reproduced with the same go toolchain installed to /usr/local/go, work dir, and GOPATH
installation_standard_variables_justific: Makefile includes PREFIX and DESTDIR env vars.
installation_development_quick_justifica: Instructions for doing this are documented in https://git.sr.ht/~seirdy/moac/tree/master/CONTRIBUTING.md
external_dependencies_justification: External deps are listed in go.sum at https://git.sr.ht/~seirdy/moac/tree/master/item/go.sum and in the project README at https://git.sr.ht/~seirdy/moac/tree/master/item/README.md
dependency_monitoring_justification: The project has a Makefile job that scans dependencies for CVEs using sonatype's "nancy" linter, powered by Sonatype's OSS Index. That job gets run in CI every commit.
updateable_reused_components_justificati:
The project only directly uses very few external deps, one of which is an official package maintained by the core Go team. Everything else is from the stdlib.

External deps are all tracked in go.mod: https://git.sr.ht/~seirdy/moac/tree/master/item/go.mod
interfaces_current_justification: The project uses no deprecated or obsolete functions/APIs.
automated_integration_testing_justificat: Evert commit pushed to every branch triggers a CI job that runs an automated test suite that reports success/failure, and updates a badge in the README to reflect the status of the tests.
regression_tests_added50_justification: The majority of closed tickets listed in https://todo.sr.ht/~seirdy/MOAC?search=status:closed that have been resolved as fixed also have test cases that will fail if the issue arises again.
test_statement_coverage80_justification: One of the build VMs measures code coverage using go's built-in test/coverage tools.
implement_secure_design_justification: The project has limited scope; it's just a library with Go functions, along with CLI utilities that read from stdin and arguments and write to stdout. There's no crossing of trust boundaries.
input_validation_justification: Inputs are checked for completeness, valid numerical ranges, and invalid/control Unicode characters in the v2 branch; this will be merged for the v2.0.0 release.
signed_releases_justification: The "Installation" section of the README links to releases which include PGP sigs, and links to the public key to use when verifying releases.
version_tags_signed_justification: All git tags are signed with the maintainer's signing key.
small_tasks_justification: Ticket tracker includes "good first issue" labels: https://todo.sr.ht/~seirdy/MOAC
test_statement_coverage90_justification: One of the build VMs measures statement coverage during tests; test coverage is currently over 90%.
